Comment (src/composables/axios/index.ts:91):
**Low (polish): 403 handler has no dedup â€” bulk actions can spam toasts + stampede `/api/me/permissions`.**

Every 403 fires its own toast *and* a `permissionsStore.hydrate()`. Because the permission model is optimistic-by-default, a single user action that fans out into N requests can produce N "Permission denied" toasts and N concurrent `GET /api/me/permissions` calls. The most reachable case is the bulk operations in `SuggestionsView` ("Accept selected" / "Reject selected" iterate over `selectedSuggestionIds`), and instance-level denies where the type-level hint allowed the click.

Suggestion: keep a single in-flight hydrate (dedupe/await a shared promise, or guard with a `hydrating` flag) and throttle the toast so one denied batch surfaces one message. The resync intent is good â€” it's just the per-response multiplication that bites.
Replies:
**lisa implementation guidance:** Agreed â€” will dedupe. Plan: (1) in src/stores/permissions.ts, guard hydrate() with a module-level in-flight Promise so N concurrent 403s collapse into a single GET /api/me/permissions (await/return the shared promise, cleared in finally); (2) in src/composables/axios/index.ts, throttle the 403 toast to one per short window (module-level timestamp, ~3s) so a fanned-out batch surfaces one "Permission denied" message. Resync + warn behaviour is unchanged.

