Comment (src/constants/permissions.ts:131):
**Nit: `permissionTooltip` falls back to raw keys for resources/actions missing from the label/verb maps.**

`RESOURCE_LABELS` omits `ai-diagnostics`, `import`, `digest` (and `ACTION_VERBS` omits `ingest`, `register`, `users.manage`/`sso.manage`/`settings.manage`). For those the tooltip renders the raw key, e.g. *"You don't have permission to ai-diagnostics ai-diagnostics."* Low impact since those are predominantly route-/`PermissionGate`-gated (no visible-but-disabled tooltip), but worth filling in the maps (or asserting completeness) so a future visible-but-disabled gate on one of them doesn't read oddly.
Replies:
**lisa implementation guidance:** Agreed (nit). Will fill the maps in src/constants/permissions.ts: add RESOURCE_LABELS for ai-diagnostics, import, digest; add ACTION_VERBS for ingest, register, and users.manage/sso.manage/settings.manage, so permissionTooltip never renders a raw key if one of those ever gets a visible-but-disabled gate.

